title: Pioneer girl cagers win 2-of-3 starts - NewsBreak
text:
By Mike Tanner, Sports Reporter ,
1 hours ago In girlsâ€™ basketball action last week, Pioneer won two games in three starts. The Panthers are 1-2 in ECIC III and 5-4 overall. On Jan. 13, Pioneer defeated visiting West Seneca East, 66-34, in an ECIC III game. The Panthers led 23-9 after one quarter and built a 38-11 halftime lead over the Trojans after a 15-2 second quarter run. The Panthers led 55-23 after three quarters, with a 17-12 third quarter run, and kept their lead in the fourth quarter, as both teams scored 11 points in the fourth quarter. Read full article
